    "The presence of an administrator group in the proposed scheme might render the system vulnerable to attacks against members of this group.In studies [9,10,16,17,21,30], patient data were recorded on the blockchain.",
    "As the size of the patient data grow, the system become inefficient.",
    "In addition, as the size of the blockchain increases, scalability decreases, and the Single Point of Failure (SPOF) problem increases.",
    "In a previous study [13], patient data were recorded on the blockchain, and a central entity called the system manager was present.",
    "In another study [28], a central entity called the Third-Party Auditor was included."
